@startuml video_download_playwright
!theme cerulean
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam participantBorderColor #333
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #999
skinparam maxMessageSize 180

title Video Download via Playwright + HLS

actor Consumer
participant "DownloadController\n/api/v1/download" as DC
participant "VideoDownloadService" as VDS
participant "PlaywrightVideoFetcher" as PVF #LightSalmon
participant "Headless Chromium\n(Playwright)" as CHROME #LightYellow
participant "Kodik Player\nkodikplayer.com" as KP #LightCoral
participant "Kodik CDN\nsolodcdn.com" as CDN #LightCoral
participant "KodikVideoDecoderService" as KVDS #LightGray
participant "WebClient\n(kodikCdnWebClient)" as WC #LightGray
database "MySQL" as DB #LightGreen
collections "Local FS\n./data/videos/" as FS #Wheat

Consumer -> DC : POST /api/v1/download/{variantId}
activate DC

DC -> VDS : downloadVariant(variantId)
activate VDS

VDS -> DB : findById(variantId)
DB --> VDS : KodikEpisodeVariant

alt Playwright available (primary strategy)

    VDS -> PVF : downloadVideo(kodikLink, targetPath)
    activate PVF

    note over PVF #E8F5E9
    **WHY Playwright?**
    solodcdn.com CDN blocks direct
    HTTP requests (returns 0 bytes).
    Only real browser context with
    proper cookies gets actual content.
    end note

    PVF -> CHROME : newContext(UA, viewport 1280x720)
    activate CHROME

    == Phase 1: Navigate to player ==

    CHROME -> KP : GET /seria/{id}/{hash}/720p
    activate KP
    KP --> CHROME : HTML + JS (player page)
    deactivate KP

    == Phase 2: Trigger playback ==

    note over PVF, CHROME
    waitForTimeout(2000ms)
    then: JS click play button selectors
    then: click center of page (640, 360)
    then: waitForTimeout(1000ms)
    then: video.play() again
    end note

    CHROME -> KP : POST /ftor\n(AJAX, triggered by player JS)
    activate KP
    KP --> CHROME : JSON with encoded video URLs
    deactivate KP

    note over CHROME : Player processes VAST ads\n(vast_ended event)

    == Phase 3: Intercept video URL ==

    CHROME -> CDN : GET /s/m/{base64path}\n(initiated by <video> element)
    note over PVF #FFFDE7
    **onResponse listener** catches
    URL matching "solodcdn.com/s/m/"
    and resolves CompletableFuture
    end note

    == Phase 4: Download via APIRequestContext ==

    note over PVF #E8F5E9
    **WHY APIRequestContext instead of fetch()?**
    Browser's fetch() is blocked by CORS.
    APIRequestContext is server-side but
    inherits cookies from BrowserContext.
    end note

    PVF -> CDN : context.request().get(videoUrl)\n(with browser cookies, bypasses CORS)
    activate CDN
    CDN --> PVF : Response body (may be HLS manifest or MP4)
    deactivate CDN

    == Phase 5: Handle response type ==

    alt Response starts with "#EXTM3U" (HLS manifest)
        note over PVF #FFF3E0
        **WHY HLS?**
        CDN returns HLS manifest (.m3u8)
        instead of MP4 for many videos.
        Manifest lists ~200-1300 .ts segments
        of ~6 seconds each.
        end note

        note over PVF #E8F5E9
        Extract cookies from BrowserContext.
        Create java.net.http.HttpClient with cookies.
        **APIRequestContext is NOT thread-safe**
        (single WebSocket), so we use HttpClient.
        end note

        par 8 threads (hlsConcurrency, configurable)
            PVF -> CDN : HttpClient.send(segment.ts)\n(with browser cookies)
            CDN --> PVF : .ts segment bytes (~300KB each)
        end

        PVF -> FS : write all segments in order (extension .ts)
    else Direct MP4 response
        PVF -> FS : write MP4 bytes
    end

    deactivate CHROME

    PVF --> VDS : filePath (absolute)
    deactivate PVF

else Playwright failed — fallback to WebClient

    note over VDS #FFEBEE
    Fallback: decode links via
    KodikVideoDecoderService,
    download via WebClient.
    **Almost always returns 0 bytes**
    due to CDN blocking.
    end note

    VDS -> KVDS : decode(kodikLink)
    KVDS --> VDS : Map<quality, cdnUrl>
    VDS -> WC : fetchWithRedirects(cdnUrl)
    WC -> CDN : GET /s/m/...
    CDN --> WC : **0 bytes** (blocked)
    WC --> VDS : empty response
    VDS --> VDS : throw "0 bytes"

end

VDS -> DB : UPDATE kodik_episode_variant\nSET local_filepath = ?
VDS --> DC : DownloadState(COMPLETED, filepath)
deactivate VDS

DC --> Consumer : 200 OK\n{"status":"COMPLETED","filepath":"..."}
deactivate DC
@enduml
